{
  "stem": "3928.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Nightly, I went up to his place, with the German commando car, and picked up American and English flyers at night, under the cover of the night.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I took over to Csepel Island.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I gave it to the partisans, who took over.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then, in turn, took whatever was necessary to take them to a, you know, either to France or England or, at the time, Italy was already-- there was American bases in Italy, to go back to their units, you know, and to save them.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That happened nights after nights after nights, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Except, one night, when I ran into a very reluctant German military police group, and they stopped my car.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "At the time, the cars had just a special slit, in the front, you know, because of the air raids.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They don't want, you know, the full light, just a small slit on the light.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They were all blacked out, the rest of them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I seen them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They're stopping me, you know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And-- they had the chain, you know, special military-- military police has a special chain, which says 'Military Police' on here.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they asked me, what's going on?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I told him, I'm taking these people to the headquarters.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So he said, what right do you have to take them to the headquarters?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I took my paper, which I made up for myself, you know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were reading this paper, you know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And as I looked at them, I see that one of the German soldiers, the military policeman, put the magazine into his machine gun.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it wasn't [LAUGHS] too many questions to ask, you know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So fortunately, I was maybe a second faster than they were.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
